# pip-audit suppressions (security-hardening-followups AC3).
#
# Format: one accepted vulnerability per non-comment line — the vuln id first, then a
# `#`-comment carrying BOTH a one-line reason AND a review-by date (or tracking issue).
# A suppression without an expiry rots: it silently masks the CVE after an upstream fix
# ships. Example:
#
#   GHSA-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx  # transitive via <pkg>, no fixed release; review-by 2026-09-30
#   PYSEC-2026-123       # dev-only (ruff), not shipped; tracking #123; review-by 2026-12-31
#
# The CI workflow feeds each id here to `pip-audit --ignore-vuln <id>`. Keep this list as
# short as the truth allows — every entry is a posture exception, not a default.
#
# (empty: the dependency closure has no accepted vulnerability at baseline.)
